<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>NASA APOD</title>

  <style>
    * {
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      box-sizing: border-box;
    }

    body {
      background-color: black;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      padding: 20px;
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    }

    h1 {
      color: white;
      font-size: 32px;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      text-align: center;
    }

    img {
      width: 80%;
      max-width: 600px;
      border: 4px solid whitesmoke;
      border-radius: 10px;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
    }

    p {
      font-size: 18px;
      color: white;
      max-width: 800px;
      text-align: center;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>HOW BEAUTIFUL IS OUR EARTH</h1>
  <img src="<%= data.url %>" alt="NASA APOD">
  <p>
    NASA's Astronomy Picture of the Day (APOD) is a daily feature that showcases stunning images of space and celestial events, often accompanied by a short explanation written by a professional astronomer. From distant galaxies and nebulae to planets and satellites, APOD helps us appreciate the wonders of the universe through breathtaking visuals and scientific insights.
  </p>
</body>
</html>
